    "narrative": "The Austin Waves face a challenging slate today, but **Gunnar Henderson** stands out as the clear anchor of the lineup with an elite score of 81.88. His massive 16% park factor boost, combined with a favorable matchup against Houser, makes him a lock for production. Following closely, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (67.80) and **Marcell Ozuna** (66.28) provide the core power upside. **Marcell Ozuna** specifically benefits from an ideal combination of a wind-out day at the ballpark and a targetable matchup against Taillon, pushing his daily efficiency well above his baseline projection.\n\nThe optimizer faced a difficult choice regarding the final bench spots, with **Coby Mayo** (54.50) serving as the most notable exclusion. While **Coby Mayo** offers significant power and a strong park factor advantage, the projected #8 spot in the order hampered his upside enough to keep him behind the more consistent output of **Jackson Merrill** and **Heliot Ramos**. We are closely monitoring the lineup postings for **Drake Baldwin**, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Miguel Vargas**, **Josh Lowe**, **Andy Pages**, **Kyle Tucker**, **Jackson Merrill**, and **Marcell Ozuna**; should these expected positions shift, particularly for our speed-heavy assets like **Josh Lowe** and **Andy Pages**, we may see further fluctuations in the daily efficiency scores.\n\nRisks today are concentrated in the bottom third of the order, specifically regarding **Andy Pages** and **Kyle Tucker**, both of whom must contend with the elite skill set of deGrom. While **Kyle Tucker** maintains a respectable 57.87 due to his high baseline, **Andy Pages** drops to 43.59, hovering near our substitution floor. Furthermore, our focus on stolen base efficiency remains a priority; **Heliot Ramos** and **Andy Pages** are both flagged for facing pitchers with high hold percentages, which may suppress their baserunning opportunities despite the need for speed in our 5x5 format. We 